      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARGARITARI (3) ran second last start at Ouyen over 1654m, beaten 7 metres. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Big chance in a similar race. CEE WHOS BETTOR NZ (8) settled handy but couldn't finish the race off and could only manage sixth last start over 1680m at Terang, that effort coming after a win at Mt Gambier the run before. Will enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw, with the sprint lane to play a big role. Meets a comparable field and he can bounce back to winning form. IMAGINATION ORO (4) is better than her last-start seventh over 1680m at Terang would suggest. Worth another chance. ALWAYS BE TECHY (7) is going well, with a minor placing two starts ago then a game third last time out over 1780m at Mt Gambier where she broke in running. Will need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position. It doesn't get any easier but she is going well enough to be competitive.",
